      "side": 0,
      "message": "`setProperties()` builds a new termios structure from scratch rather than updating the current terminal settings with `tcgetattr()`. Since the baud rate is not inherited from the existing configuration, it must always be programmed into the new termios structure before calling `tcsetattr()`. Otherwise, when only the parity changes, the speed fields remain uninitialized (effectively B0), which I observed during validation with the xr_serial driver.",
      "parentUuid": "5cd515ff_c2021267",
